1,"replyTime":"2020-02-27T10:34:29.000Z","msg":"因為而家中國入境香港既強制家居檢疫係599C regulate，所以唔under 599A，冇公佈<br />\n<br />\n當然你可以叫行家入Q問，不過肯定話數量太多，唔係密切接觸，blah blah blah"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-02-27T12:10:11.000Z","msg":"A同C 有咩分別🙇&zwj;♂️"},{"pid":"293f2e8f6114ca98d7687abc9eef3d84d28a9bbe","tid":1895101,"uid":135274,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f7a12797f3b6da3f8a7928adbe935b5fd7eb04d2","tid":1895101,"uid":164477,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f12dc9ae848fda5ebd1e03330d551f8838d1d7c1","tid":1895101,"uid":135274,"like":7,"dislike":0,"score":7,"quote":{"pid":"8a4bf5de45b2b18a03ffc3b500eeca38f5a2b22c","tid":1895101,"uid":13767,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-02-27T09:25:44.000Z","msg":"即係唔公佈??"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-02-27T10:34:29.000Z","msg":"因為而家中國入境香港既強制家居檢疫係599C regulate，所以唔under 599A，冇公佈<br />\n<br />\n當然你可以叫行家入Q問，不過肯定話數量太多，唔係密切接觸，blah blah blah"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-02-27T12:10:11.000Z","msg":"A同C 有咩分別🙇&zwj;♂️"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-02-27T13:55:39.000Z","msg":"Cap 599A is a subsidiary legislation under Cap 599. It grants health officers the power to place a person under quarantine if he is a contact. In other words, it only covers those who have got in touch with an infected person, eg. family members, but not those coming back from China.<br />\n<br />\nThus, the HKSAR government relies on Cap 599 to make a public health emergency regulation, ie Cap 599C, to place all people coming back from China under quarantine.<br />\n<br />\nAnother difference between Cap 599A and Cap 599C is that the latter is an emergency regulation which has an expiry date, while the former is a general subsidiary legislation indicative of how Cap 599 shall be implemented."}]}